WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:50.170 --> 00:01:52.460
Mr. Iceburg

3
00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:55.970
This is great!

4
00:01:55.970 --> 00:01:58.540
Hey! I'm counting on you!

5
00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:03.640
Who would've imagined these creatures
could be so convenient!

6
00:02:03.640 --> 00:02:05.930
It's a pretty smooth ride. Comfy, too!

7
00:02:06.800 --> 00:02:08.270
To the right! Right!

8
00:02:08.270 --> 00:02:10.190
The ball is headed your way! Here we go!

9
00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:14.360
Ah! Stop the ball!

10
00:02:19.660 --> 00:02:22.250
Pass the ball! Pass the ball!

11
00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:22.250
So cool!

12
00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:30.210
Looks like a residential area.

13
00:02:31.690 --> 00:02:35.620
This town was certainly built
with canals in mind.

14
00:02:42.510 --> 00:02:43.700
Huh?

15
00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:48.700
Ah, there's an incline. Will we make it
if we go against the current?

16
00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:50.440
Can we go up?

17
00:02:56.390 --> 00:02:58.490
Wait! Wrong way! Go right! Right!

18
00:02:58.490 --> 00:03:02.230
They can even go uphill
against the water, huh?

19
00:03:02.230 --> 00:03:03.950
Not bad, you guys!

20
00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:09.790
There are canals even on the rooftops!

21
00:03:09.790 --> 00:03:14.880
But we're going the wrong way!
We have to go to the shopping district first!

22
00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:17.150
Oh? What's the hurry?

23
00:03:17.150 --> 00:03:20.340
It's not every day you get to
walk along the canals.

24
00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:25.300
H-Hey! L-Look! Look ahead!

25
00:03:26.130 --> 00:03:29.600
Oh, that's right! We're at the top of the hill!

26
00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:31.810
Which... would mean...

27
00:03:49.290 --> 00:03:50.960
We're flying!

28
00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:52.780
We're falling. We're falling.
We're falling. We're falling.

29
00:03:52.780 --> 00:03:53.790
We're falling. We're falling. We're falling.

30
00:03:53.790 --> 00:03:58.760
– We're falling!
– We're falling!

31
00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:09.180
Don't be so reckless!

32
00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:14.650
Huh?

33
00:04:15.400 --> 00:04:17.490
Miss! Our goods are cheap!

34
00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:20.650
How about taking a look at our products?

35
00:04:24.610 --> 00:04:27.580
We have lots of rare, quality items!

36
00:04:27.580 --> 00:04:30.610
Now starting our fifty-percent-off sale!

37
00:04:31.540 --> 00:04:34.800
Wow! This place got lively!

38
00:04:34.800 --> 00:04:37.290
Oh? We ended up in the shopping district!

39
00:04:37.290 --> 00:04:39.920
So what you took was actually a shortcut?

40
00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:45.420
Sorry! You guys are pretty smart after all!

41
00:04:45.420 --> 00:04:49.290
I've never been to such
an energetic shopping district!

42
00:04:49.290 --> 00:04:50.900
Hey, check it out!

43
00:04:50.900 --> 00:04:52.700
That bull is huge!

44
00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:55.350
Whoa! Hey, it's headed this way!

45
00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.000
This guy is scary!

46
00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:04.200
He'd eat us whole!

47
00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:06.320
I wonder if it's a king size.

48
00:05:07.280 --> 00:05:09.240
Huh? What's up with them?

49
00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:12.120
Masks...?

50
00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:14.700
Wow, they're so elegant!

51
00:05:14.700 --> 00:05:16.580
Think it's some kind of party?

52
00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:20.040
What? What's going on?

53
00:05:21.090 --> 00:05:24.550
Come and get 'em!
Hot and fresh hydro takoyaki!

54
00:05:25.550 --> 00:05:28.010
So, that's two hydro croquettes?

55
00:05:28.010 --> 00:05:32.060
Both look yummy! Yagara, go over that way.

56
00:05:32.470 --> 00:05:34.890
Hey! What's the big idea?!

57
00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:37.000
Hey, Luffy! Where are you going?!

58
00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:39.270
Ask the yagara!

59
00:05:45.740 --> 00:05:48.280
Welcome! What'll it be?

60
00:05:48.280 --> 00:05:51.490
Oh, so you were hungry.

61
00:05:51.490 --> 00:05:56.100
Although it's normally for people,
hydro meat is a yagara's favorite food.

62
00:05:56.100 --> 00:05:58.210
Hydro? Then gimme ten!

63
00:05:59.300 --> 00:06:02.990
They're so good the cooks from
Gourmet Town buy them in secret.

64
00:06:02.990 --> 00:06:05.390
It satisfies both body and soul, doesn't it?

65
00:06:08.300 --> 00:06:13.100
They... are... so... soft!

66
00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:13.940
Yummy!

67
00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:17.290
What?! It's that good?!
Hey, Luffy! Toss one over here!

68
00:06:17.290 --> 00:06:19.900
No! Go buy your own!

69
00:06:19.900 --> 00:06:20.990
Huh?

70
00:06:20.990 --> 00:06:23.860
Hey, Nami! Pull the boat over to that shop!

71
00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:28.150
More masks? They seem to be all over town.

72
00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:30.950
And those wearing the masks...

73
00:06:32.900 --> 00:06:35.390
Hey, Nami!

74
00:06:37.390 --> 00:06:38.340
Okay!

75
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:42.850
For the last leg of our trip to Shipyard Island,
we'll travel up a water gate elevator.

76
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:46.840
A water gate elevator?

77
00:06:46.840 --> 00:06:49.240
It's that tower-like thing.

78
00:06:55.890 --> 00:06:58.050
Make your way inside, please!

79
00:06:58.770 --> 00:07:02.730
The elevator leads up to Shipyard Island,

80
00:07:02.730 --> 00:07:10.700
where you'll find the shipyards
and downtown Water Seven!

81
00:07:11.410 --> 00:07:14.090
Please make your way inside the gate!

82
00:07:14.090 --> 00:07:17.150
One minute until it closes!

83
00:07:18.660 --> 00:07:21.620
What's gonna happen inside?

84
00:07:27.550 --> 00:07:30.050
Whoa! They closed the gate behind us!

85
00:07:31.210 --> 00:07:33.460
We're going up!
We're going up! We're going up!

86
00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:41.400
I see. That happens. Then this happens.

87
00:07:41.400 --> 00:07:44.520
Then it's this and that,
which makes it a water gate elevator.

88
00:07:44.520 --> 00:07:48.480
Whoa! Water Seven is pretty neat!

89
00:07:49.890 --> 00:07:52.960
So they use water for all sorts of things!

90
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.580
Hey!

91
00:08:00.580 --> 00:08:03.540
Who're you callin' "moss head"?

92
00:08:04.600 --> 00:08:05.540
Hey, Zoro.

93
00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:10.530
Where's Robin? She isn't on the ship.

94
00:08:10.530 --> 00:08:12.510
Mm-hm.

95
00:08:12.510 --> 00:08:16.970
That's right. She and Chopper
headed out earlier.

96
00:08:16.970 --> 00:08:17.930
What?!

97
00:08:17.930 --> 00:08:20.540
She said she was going shopping.

98
00:08:20.540 --> 00:08:24.400
What the hell?! Then you're
the only one on the ship?!

99
00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:27.590
What a letdown!

100
00:08:27.590 --> 00:08:29.420
You got that right.

101
00:08:30.990 --> 00:08:34.070
All right, then. I'm going grocery shopping.

102
00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:36.640
Watch the ship while I'm gone.

103
00:08:39.540 --> 00:08:42.300
Hell, he's already asleep.

104
00:08:42.300 --> 00:08:44.910
Whatever. She's all yours.

105
00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:16.740
We're here!

106
00:09:20.200 --> 00:09:25.460
So this is downtown Water Seven
and the world's greatest shipyard?!

107
00:09:31.610 --> 00:09:34.800
It looks like there's more land
than water around here.

108
00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:41.430
Everything's so huge!

109
00:09:43.180 --> 00:09:46.140
I've never seen such a big city!

110
00:09:54.570 --> 00:09:55.510
Huh?

111
00:09:55.510 --> 00:09:57.600
What's with that crowd?

112
00:09:57.600 --> 00:09:59.600
Are they gawking at the shipyard?

113
00:09:59.600 --> 00:10:03.040
Let's check it out! Go, yagara!

114
00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:14.000
Hey, look over there!
It's Lucci! He's so handsome!

115
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:16.490
Isn't Paulie here?

116
00:10:16.490 --> 00:10:22.140
Lulu's here! So suave!
He's truly a man among men.

117
00:10:22.140 --> 00:10:25.600
But nobody's manlier than Tilestone!

118
00:10:26.780 --> 00:10:28.560
Hey, pops.

119
00:10:27.890 --> 00:10:28.560
Hm?

120
00:10:28.560 --> 00:10:30.150
Did something happen?

121
00:10:30.150 --> 00:10:35.700
Yeah, some pirates tried stirring
up trouble at Dock One again.

122
00:10:35.700 --> 00:10:40.180
But, it ended with the craftsmen
knocking them out, as usual.

123
00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:42.070
There's no end to these idiots.

124
00:10:42.070 --> 00:10:45.790
The shipwrights can beat up pirates?

125
00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:48.010
Oh, you must be a seafarer.

126
00:10:48.010 --> 00:10:51.580
That crowd... Well, they're just busybodies.

127
00:10:52.380 --> 00:10:57.050
Everyone 'round here admires
the Galley-La Company shipwrights.

128
00:10:57.050 --> 00:10:59.050
They're strong...

129
00:10:59.720 --> 00:11:00.970
and skilled.

130
00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:04.930
They're the pride of Water Seven.

131
00:11:08.430 --> 00:11:10.850
Wow! I can't wait to meet them!

132
00:11:11.770 --> 00:11:13.810
Hey, Luffy!

133
00:11:13.810 --> 00:11:15.190
Huh?

134
00:11:15.190 --> 00:11:17.600
Let's hurry up and get to
the currency exchange.

135
00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:19.890
We can come back here later.

136
00:11:20.370 --> 00:11:21.780
Okay!

137
00:11:26.330 --> 00:11:33.170
Backstreets Shopping District
Water Seven

138
00:11:33.690 --> 00:11:35.890
This is the Backstreets shopping district.

139
00:11:35.890 --> 00:11:40.220
They call a place this lively the Backstreets?

140
00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:43.490
There're also places where we can walk, huh?

141
00:11:43.490 --> 00:11:45.900
Clear water that matches a pristine city...

142
00:11:45.900 --> 00:11:47.180
Yeah.

143
00:11:50.140 --> 00:11:52.690
Whoa! What's that?!

144
00:11:52.690 --> 00:11:54.340
That's a mask shop.

145
00:11:55.860 --> 00:12:00.300
I've noticed people are walking
around town wearing those masks.

146
00:12:00.300 --> 00:12:04.320
Oh, they're wearing masks?
I just thought they had weird faces.

147
00:12:07.850 --> 00:12:10.490
It seems San Faldo is
holding a costume festival.

148
00:12:10.490 --> 00:12:13.250
It's an island you can reach
using the sea train.

149
00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:16.150
What? How do you know that?

150
00:12:16.150 --> 00:12:18.650
People walking by are talking about it.

151
00:12:19.800 --> 00:12:22.260
I'm surprised that you can hear them.

152
00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:23.610
It's a habit.

153
00:12:24.900 --> 00:12:29.880
Since childhood, I survived by listening
to those around me and gauging their feelings.

154
00:12:31.790 --> 00:12:33.980
You're amazing, Robin.

155
00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:41.780
Doctor...

156
00:12:41.780 --> 00:12:42.950
Hm?

157
00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:45.500
Over there! It's a bookstore.

158
00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:47.120
Really?!

159
00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:49.030
Can we?!

160
00:12:50.100 --> 00:12:52.120
Of course! Let's go inside.

161
00:12:52.760 --> 00:12:54.080
Yay!

162
00:13:06.550 --> 00:13:08.680
I'm with CP9.

163
00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:27.320
Robin! I'm gonna go in, okay?

164
00:13:55.140 --> 00:13:59.150
It should be fine if I'm in my human form.

165
00:13:59.150 --> 00:14:00.650
Oh?

166
00:14:00.650 --> 00:14:05.390
Wow, what a neat mask!
What're you dressed up as?

167
00:14:05.390 --> 00:14:08.610
Oh, y'know... A human reindeer.

168
00:14:11.210 --> 00:14:12.530
Glad you're having fun.

169
00:14:15.590 --> 00:14:16.540
Oh?

170
00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:24.380
Robin?

171
00:14:25.280 --> 00:14:26.690
Hey!

172
00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:29.860
Robin?!

173
00:15:05.510 --> 00:15:08.630
We thought we'd get you while you slept.

174
00:15:12.590 --> 00:15:14.480
Who are you creeps?!

175
00:15:15.500 --> 00:15:16.930
Identify yourselves!

176
00:15:16.930 --> 00:15:20.080
O-One hundred million belly?!

177
00:15:17.470 --> 00:15:23.900
Currency Exchange

178
00:15:20.080 --> 00:15:23.900
I-Idiot! You're too loud!
Everyone can hear you!

179
00:15:23.900 --> 00:15:26.370
Y-Y-You're gonna give us that much money?!

180
00:15:26.370 --> 00:15:29.860
L-Like... Like I said, Luffy, you're too loud!

181
00:15:30.690 --> 00:15:32.910
This is indeed worth that much.

182
00:15:32.910 --> 00:15:36.870
This is incredibly pure gold
with historical significance.

183
00:15:36.870 --> 00:15:39.990
With that much money,
we can really fix the Merry!

184
00:15:39.990 --> 00:15:42.090
Yeah! With money to spare!

185
00:15:42.090 --> 00:15:45.330
Nice! Then we use the rest
to buy a bronze statue!

186
00:15:45.330 --> 00:15:46.780
No. No, we won't.

187
00:15:46.780 --> 00:15:51.140
If you accept that amount, please sign
and put your thumbprint here.

188
00:15:51.140 --> 00:15:54.220
I'll go prepare the cash immediately.

189
00:15:54.220 --> 00:15:57.180
Okay! I'll put however
many thumbprints you want!

190
00:15:57.180 --> 00:16:00.020
If that's not enough, I'll put mine, too!

191
00:16:09.650 --> 00:16:12.310
Wait. What's the matter, Nami?

192
00:16:12.310 --> 00:16:17.920
There are three things
I want to say, Mr. Appraiser.

193
00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:19.580
First...

194
00:16:19.580 --> 00:16:23.790
I forgot to mention that this guy's got
a 100-million-berry bounty on his head.

195
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:26.750
Second...

196
00:16:26.750 --> 00:16:30.090
The appraisal you just
gave us is unacceptable.

197
00:16:30.090 --> 00:16:33.260
Third... If you lie to us again...

198
00:16:34.010 --> 00:16:36.010
your head is ours.

199
00:16:36.010 --> 00:16:37.220
That is all.

200
00:16:37.220 --> 00:16:38.520
Please...!

201
00:16:38.520 --> 00:16:41.390
Please forgive me!

202
00:16:41.390 --> 00:16:46.400
Th-Three hundred million belly?!
I'm not dreaming, am I?!

203
00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:50.320
Our adventure on Sky Island
has finally paid off!

204
00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:52.530
I'm super rich!

205
00:16:52.530 --> 00:16:53.650
– You mean "we"!
– You mean "we"!

206
00:16:53.660 --> 00:16:56.800
P-Please come again!

207
00:16:56.800 --> 00:17:01.350
I-I-I-It became 300 million! I-I'm scared!

208
00:17:01.350 --> 00:17:03.660
I'm carrying 100 million?

209
00:17:03.660 --> 00:17:07.440
Wow, Nami's real good at
making scary threats, huh?

210
00:17:07.440 --> 00:17:11.700
I estimated it at about this much
from the start, but then he told us "100 million."

211
00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:14.800
You two couldn't play it cool,
so he tried to pull a fast one.

212
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:18.510
Hey, Luffy! You shouldn't
swing it around like that!

213
00:17:18.510 --> 00:17:22.470
Well, anyway, I'm glad it went well.

214
00:17:23.480 --> 00:17:26.440
– Ahh! The river!
– Ahh! The river!

215
00:17:26.440 --> 00:17:29.980
We're gonna lose 100 million belly to the river!

216
00:17:32.600 --> 00:17:35.030
Phew! That was close!

217
00:17:37.320 --> 00:17:41.090
I'm gonna knock you out!

218
00:17:38.010 --> 00:17:41.090
I'm gonna break your teeth, you asshole!

219
00:17:42.190 --> 00:17:46.620
I-I'm... I'm sorry.

220
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.810
"Identify yourselves"?

221
00:18:02.810 --> 00:18:05.060
Pirate Hunter Zoro...

222
00:18:09.060 --> 00:18:12.990
We're bounty hunters whose name
quiets even a crying child—

223
00:18:13.530 --> 00:18:15.940
the Franky Family!

224
00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:20.980
Your head's worth 60 million!
We'll gratefully take it.

225
00:18:20.980 --> 00:18:23.910
Then, we'll wait in ambush inside your ship...

226
00:18:23.910 --> 00:18:26.710
and catch the entire crew in one swoop.

227
00:18:28.490 --> 00:18:30.630
We'll make a killing! How lucky!

228
00:18:32.780 --> 00:18:33.960
I'm first!

229
00:18:36.810 --> 00:18:38.080
"Lucky"?

230
00:18:41.010 --> 00:18:42.970
You mean unlucky, right?

231
00:18:50.100 --> 00:18:52.060
Stand tall!

232
00:18:52.770 --> 00:18:54.020
Two-Sword Style:

233
00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:58.120
Rhino Cycle!

234
00:19:09.510 --> 00:19:11.040
Dumbasses.

235
00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:14.960
Dammit!

236
00:19:17.920 --> 00:19:21.930
S-S-Say, Nami... Maybe we really
should take it back to the ship.

237
00:19:21.930 --> 00:19:25.890
That'd be a waste of time.
The shipyard is right over this hill.

238
00:19:25.890 --> 00:19:29.850
Hey, I'm a bit shocked you guys
won't let me near the money.

239
00:19:29.850 --> 00:19:32.250
Once we meet a shipwright,

240
00:19:32.250 --> 00:19:37.320
we'll need to go back to the Merry with him
right away for the repair estimate.

241
00:19:37.780 --> 00:19:39.320
I see.

242
00:19:39.320 --> 00:19:40.780
That seems about right.

243
00:19:40.780 --> 00:19:44.900
I'm really not sure how to act.
I've never carried around so much cash.

244
00:19:44.900 --> 00:19:47.300
Well, that's only natural.

245
00:19:47.300 --> 00:19:49.860
What's unnatural is someone flailing it around.

246
00:19:49.860 --> 00:19:52.540
Ah! Hey, look over there!
They're selling hydro buns!

247
00:19:52.540 --> 00:19:53.380
Let's buy 100!

248
00:19:53.380 --> 00:19:54.060
– Shut up.
– Shut up.

249
00:19:54.060 --> 00:19:55.010
Then, let's buy 1,000!

250
00:19:55.010 --> 00:19:55.700
– Shut up.
– Shut up.

251
00:19:55.700 --> 00:19:56.010
Then...

252
00:19:56.010 --> 00:19:57.120
– Shut up!
– Shut up!

253
00:19:57.120 --> 00:19:58.690
O-Okay...

254
00:20:11.690 --> 00:20:15.780
Here we are... back at the shipyard entrance.

255
00:20:17.600 --> 00:20:22.610
Good! Looks like the crowd
from earlier is gone.

256
00:20:22.610 --> 00:20:27.620
Anyway, let's find... um... uh...
What's his name again?

257
00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:29.190
Mr. Iceburg.

258
00:20:29.190 --> 00:20:31.700
Right, that's it! Iceguy!

259
00:20:31.700 --> 00:20:33.640
I wonder who he is...

260
00:20:33.640 --> 00:20:37.560
The old station lady told us to talk to him.

261
00:20:37.560 --> 00:20:38.590
Yeah, she did...

262
00:20:38.590 --> 00:20:42.590
More importantly,
are we good to just walk on in?

263
00:20:42.590 --> 00:20:44.410
I'm coming in!

264
00:20:44.410 --> 00:20:45.430
– Not again!
– Not again!

265
00:20:46.800 --> 00:20:49.060
Halt!

266
00:20:48.040 --> 00:20:49.060
Hm?

267
00:20:49.060 --> 00:20:50.600
Hold your horses.

268
00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:52.100
Not a local?

269
00:20:52.770 --> 00:20:56.100
In that case, we'll converse outside.

270
00:20:57.370 --> 00:21:01.320
Only authorized individuals
can amble about the shipyard.

271
00:21:04.360 --> 00:21:06.620
Oopsie-daisy.

272
00:21:06.740 --> 00:21:11.830
Kaku
Shipwright
Galley-La Company

273
00:21:09.290 --> 00:21:11.830
Do you have some business at this dock?

274
00:21:11.830 --> 00:21:13.600
Oh, it's you, Usopp.

275
00:21:13.600 --> 00:21:16.500
Hey! I'm right here, Luffy!

276
00:21:16.500 --> 00:21:18.790
Right! The nose is square-ish!

277
00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:20.720
Oh, yeah! Um...

278
00:21:21.010 --> 00:21:23.690
We'd like to see Mr. Iceburg.

279
00:21:23.690 --> 00:21:26.130
Mr. Iceburg, you say? Are you a patron?

280
00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:28.700
Why, it's plain as day.

281
00:21:28.700 --> 00:21:32.060
It appears to be a referral
from old dame Kokoro at Shift Station.

282
00:21:32.060 --> 00:21:35.090
Wha...? Are you old or something?

283
00:21:35.090 --> 00:21:36.800
I'm twenty-three.

284
00:21:36.800 --> 00:21:40.950
For a twenty-three-year-old
you sure talk like an old geezer.

285
00:21:41.960 --> 00:21:43.290
Folks often tell me that.

286
00:21:43.290 --> 00:21:45.900
So, do you know this Iceburg person?

287
00:21:45.900 --> 00:21:51.870
Know him? Why, Mr. Iceburg
is the mayor of Water Seven.

288
00:21:51.870 --> 00:21:55.710
Huh... So he's some kinda big shot.

289
00:21:55.710 --> 00:22:02.500
Not only is he the mayor, he's the president
of Galley-La Company and manages the sea train.

290
00:22:02.500 --> 00:22:04.100
So he's the top guy here!

291
00:22:04.100 --> 00:22:07.840
Why, in Water Seven, there isn't
a soul who doesn't know him.

292
00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:09.800
Where do we go to meet him?

293
00:22:09.800 --> 00:22:12.720
Oh... Where to find him right now...

294
00:22:12.720 --> 00:22:17.190
He's always buzzing about,
which makes him a hard man to pin down.

295
00:22:17.190 --> 00:22:20.670
Aw! Can't you reach out to him for us?

296
00:22:20.670 --> 00:22:23.740
I suppose it's possible... Is the matter urgent?

297
00:22:23.740 --> 00:22:25.900
It's not that we're in a hurry, but...

298
00:22:27.110 --> 00:22:31.870
Essentially, you eager beavers want to talk
about having your ship repaired, right?

299
00:22:31.870 --> 00:22:33.920
Where did you drop anchor?

300
00:22:33.920 --> 00:22:35.700
Uh... Some place called Rocky Cape.

301
00:22:35.700 --> 00:22:40.950
Okey dokey. I'll pop on over
and survey your ship's condition.

302
00:22:40.950 --> 00:22:44.250
It'll save some time when you see Mr. Iceburg.

303
00:22:44.250 --> 00:22:46.880
You can talk about the repair fee, too.

304
00:22:46.880 --> 00:22:50.470
"Pop on over"? As in, on a yagara bull?

305
00:22:52.390 --> 00:22:56.730
If I do that, you'll be waiting
a month of Sundays.

306
00:22:56.730 --> 00:22:58.440
Ten minutes, and I'll be back.

307
00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:00.440
Ten minutes?

308
00:23:00.440 --> 00:23:03.110
Precisely. Ten minutes.

309
00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:07.820
Whoa!

310
00:23:09.780 --> 00:23:11.740
– He's fast!
– Wh-Whoa!

311
00:23:14.830 --> 00:23:17.790
Ahhh! He jumped!

312
00:23:19.790 --> 00:23:23.250
What?! But wait! Over there...

313
00:23:23.250 --> 00:23:24.670
– ...is a drop-off!
– ...is a drop-off!

314
00:23:24.670 --> 00:23:26.630
He fell!

315
00:23:35.600 --> 00:23:37.310
Amazing!

316
00:23:37.310 --> 00:23:39.100
Is he okay?

317
00:23:39.790 --> 00:23:41.020
He runs...

318
00:23:41.020 --> 00:23:43.140
freely through town.

319
00:23:43.140 --> 00:23:44.280
– What?
– What?

320
00:23:44.280 --> 00:23:44.980
Huh?

321
00:23:44.980 --> 00:23:46.980
Known as the Mountain Wind...

322
00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:52.910
he's one of the foremen of
Galley-La Company's Dock One:

323
00:23:54.870 --> 00:23:55.830
Kaku.

324
00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:03.790
Well, well. I see.

325
00:24:03.790 --> 00:24:07.340
The City of Water... This is amazing!

326
00:24:08.220 --> 00:24:12.700
Clear springs and rivers...
Clean streets and lively crowds...

327
00:24:12.700 --> 00:24:15.190
And many pretty women!

328
00:24:15.190 --> 00:24:20.770
I wanna take Nami or Robin
out in a town like this!

329
00:24:20.770 --> 00:24:23.980
Having a beauty on each arm
would be nice too.

330
00:24:26.290 --> 00:24:29.600
This side is Nami, and this side is Robin.

331
00:24:29.600 --> 00:24:31.240
Hey, mister.

332
00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:32.900
Stop making that weird face.

333
00:24:32.900 --> 00:24:35.500
So which hydro cabbage are you gonna buy?

334
00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:37.870
Which...? Ah, yes, I'll buy both.

335
00:24:37.870 --> 00:24:39.160
Oh, and ma'am...

336
00:24:39.800 --> 00:24:43.120
I'm looking for this town's
in-season food... What's available?

337
00:24:43.830 --> 00:24:47.090
Let's see. Huh? What the heck?

338
00:24:47.090 --> 00:24:49.590
Anyway, it's not so easy
getting around on foot.

339
00:24:52.780 --> 00:24:55.940
Another dead end? What a drag.

340
00:24:55.940 --> 00:24:58.930
Did I get lost? This is no good.

341
00:24:58.930 --> 00:25:02.490
That's too much like a certain swordsmoron.

342
00:25:02.490 --> 00:25:03.770
Huh?

343
00:25:09.320 --> 00:25:12.280
Oh! Robin!

344
00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:18.610
Hello! It's me! Yoo-hoo!
Robin my lo– Ah, uh... Huh?

345
00:25:18.610 --> 00:25:20.100
What the...?

346
00:25:21.810 --> 00:25:23.500
She disappeared...

347
00:25:23.500 --> 00:25:25.590
with no doors or walkways...?

348
00:25:26.880 --> 00:25:29.290
Did she fly or something?

349
00:25:29.290 --> 00:25:29.880
Huh?

350
00:25:33.080 --> 00:25:34.380
Usopp...?

351
00:25:35.400 --> 00:25:40.140
This town is a bit off.
Or am I the one who's off here?

352
00:25:52.690 --> 00:25:56.230
Why, that must be the ship.

353
00:25:59.710 --> 00:26:00.910
Pardon me.

354
00:26:04.340 --> 00:26:06.870
Oh, it's just Usopp.

355
00:26:06.870 --> 00:26:10.470
I see. It's damaged.

356
00:26:15.110 --> 00:26:17.340
The mast needs to be replaced, too.

357
00:26:19.300 --> 00:26:21.080
Usopp...?

358
00:26:22.560 --> 00:26:25.710
Hold it! Who the hell are you?!

359
00:26:25.710 --> 00:26:28.520
Oh, forgive me. I interrupted your catnap.

360
00:26:29.240 --> 00:26:31.680
Oh, man! What a surprise!

361
00:26:31.680 --> 00:26:33.940
He jumped from there!

362
00:26:33.940 --> 00:26:37.530
Well... my shipwrights are
anything but ordinary.

363
00:26:37.530 --> 00:26:39.010
So, who's this guy?

364
00:26:39.010 --> 00:26:39.890
Beats me.

365
00:26:39.890 --> 00:26:43.690
If one so wishes to speedily build
a faster, more capable vessel,

366
00:26:43.690 --> 00:26:46.800
ordinary physical abilities just won't do.

367
00:26:46.800 --> 00:26:48.090
Kalifa, before we begin...

368
00:26:48.090 --> 00:26:49.500
Yes, I've already checked.

369
00:26:50.810 --> 00:26:55.460
Straw Hat Luffy,
Pirate Hunter Zoro, Nico Robin...

370
00:26:56.420 --> 00:26:59.090
Three members of his crew have bounties.

371
00:26:59.090 --> 00:27:01.990
Total bounty: 239 million belly.

372
00:27:01.990 --> 00:27:03.430
Founded in the East Blue.

373
00:27:03.430 --> 00:27:07.090
Known as the Straw Hats,
seven crew members strong.

374
00:27:07.090 --> 00:27:09.390
Th-They have us made.

375
00:27:09.390 --> 00:27:11.450
I see. I'm glad you came.

376
00:27:09.480 --> 00:27:14.400
Iceburg
Water Seven Mayor
&
Galley-La Company President

377
00:27:11.450 --> 00:27:14.400
I'm Iceburg, the boss of this city.

378
00:27:14.400 --> 00:27:17.400
And this is a mouse I found earlier.

379
00:27:17.400 --> 00:27:19.500
His name is... let's see...

380
00:27:19.500 --> 00:27:21.320
Tyrannosaurus.

381
00:27:21.320 --> 00:27:23.300
I have to prepare his food and cage.

382
00:27:23.300 --> 00:27:25.700
Already taken care of, Mr. Iceburg.

383
00:27:25.700 --> 00:27:27.330
Well, that's Kalifa for you.

384
00:27:27.330 --> 00:27:29.600
Thank you, sir.

385
00:27:29.600 --> 00:27:30.550
Be advised,

386
00:27:30.550 --> 00:27:34.950
in ten minutes, you're to dine with a glassware
factory executive at the hotel in Chiza.

387
00:27:34.950 --> 00:27:37.590
After that, you'll give a speech at Liguria Plaza.

388
00:27:37.590 --> 00:27:41.950
When that's done, you have a conference with
Mayor Bimine of Pucci, the Gourmet Town.

389
00:27:41.950 --> 00:27:44.760
Their newspaper will also interview you.

390
00:27:44.760 --> 00:27:49.480
Finally, you'll need to return to
the office to finish a little paperwork.

391
00:27:50.120 --> 00:27:51.500
I don't want to!

392
00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:54.730
Very well. I'll cancel them all.

393
00:27:54.730 --> 00:27:56.650
Hey! Is that okay?!

394
00:27:56.650 --> 00:28:00.230
With all this clout, I can
occasionally do something like that.

395
00:28:00.230 --> 00:28:03.300
You're completely unfit to be a mayor.

396
00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:05.510
That's pretty selfish of you!

397
00:28:05.510 --> 00:28:08.800
So this guy is the one
that old lady was talking about?

398
00:28:08.800 --> 00:28:10.620
Yeah, he's that guy.

399
00:28:10.620 --> 00:28:12.290
How shameless!

400
00:28:19.400 --> 00:28:21.000
What'd you do that for?!

401
00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:22.010
Holy crap!

402
00:28:28.230 --> 00:28:31.240
How dare you refer to one of the world's

403
00:28:28.350 --> 00:28:33.480
Kalifa
Iceburg's Beautiful Secretary

404
00:28:31.240 --> 00:28:33.480
leading shipwrights as "this guy" or "that guy"!?

405
00:28:33.480 --> 00:28:34.980
What's going on?

406
00:28:34.980 --> 00:28:37.550
The secretary Kalifa had
one of her rare explosions!

407
00:28:37.550 --> 00:28:38.980
I wanna be kicked by her, too.

408
00:28:38.980 --> 00:28:42.490
Pardon me. I lost my
composure for a moment.

409
00:28:42.490 --> 00:28:46.910
Regardless, Mr. Iceburg is a local celebrity.
Please mind your manners.

410
00:28:46.910 --> 00:28:49.540
Try not to get Kalifa angry.

411
00:28:49.540 --> 00:28:51.160
When she gets angry...

412
00:28:51.160 --> 00:28:53.920
she is indiscriminate.

413
00:28:54.910 --> 00:28:57.130
You kicked your own boss too!

414
00:28:57.130 --> 00:28:58.380
Mind your own manners!

415
00:28:58.880 --> 00:29:02.470
Ah, but anyway, you're Mr. Iceburg, right?

416
00:29:03.260 --> 00:29:05.340
Please look at this. It's a referral.

417
00:29:05.340 --> 00:29:07.900
From old lady Kokoro...?

418
00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:10.310
"Take a look at their ship," huh...?

419
00:29:11.000 --> 00:29:12.310
Ah!

420
00:29:12.310 --> 00:29:16.490
What?! You won't?! Please!
Please repair our ship!

421
00:29:16.490 --> 00:29:18.200
We have money!

422
00:29:18.200 --> 00:29:20.900
The Merry is all beat up after our voyages!

423
00:29:20.900 --> 00:29:23.240
C'mon, boss!

424
00:29:22.690 --> 00:29:23.240
Okay.

425
00:29:23.240 --> 00:29:25.700
Just like that! So it's okay?!

426
00:29:25.280 --> 00:29:25.700
Yep.

427
00:29:25.700 --> 00:29:27.700
Then why did you rip it up?

428
00:29:27.700 --> 00:29:29.710
I can't stand her lipstick mark.

429
00:29:29.710 --> 00:29:32.450
Old lady Kokoro and I go
way back as drinking buddies.

430
00:29:32.450 --> 00:29:35.900
Well, that aside, Kaku has
already left to make an assessment.

431
00:29:35.900 --> 00:29:38.420
The matter is well underway. Don't fret.

432
00:29:40.480 --> 00:29:43.010
I was bored today anyway.

433
00:29:43.010 --> 00:29:44.690
Want a tour of the shipyard?

434
00:29:44.690 --> 00:29:46.280
Whoa! Seriously?

435
00:29:46.280 --> 00:29:47.390
Well then, follow me.

436
00:29:47.390 --> 00:29:50.350
This is the same man who just
canceled his appointments...

437
00:29:50.350 --> 00:29:52.600
All right! We're gonna see the shipyard!

438
00:29:53.790 --> 00:29:55.560
Oh, right. The money.

439
00:29:56.400 --> 00:29:58.500
The money...? What?

440
00:29:58.500 --> 00:30:00.570
What? What? What?

441
00:30:00.570 --> 00:30:02.480
What?!

442
00:30:03.450 --> 00:30:06.450
Hm? Everything okay, Usopp?

443
00:30:07.200 --> 00:30:10.450
Th-Th-The money... The money is gone!

444
00:30:10.450 --> 00:30:11.910
What?!

445
00:30:11.910 --> 00:30:13.360
Look everywhere!

446
00:30:13.360 --> 00:30:16.910
It's gone! I can't find it anywhere!

447
00:30:14.190 --> 00:30:16.910
Wha...? Huh?

448
00:30:17.460 --> 00:30:18.830
Ah!

449
00:30:18.830 --> 00:30:21.150
Ah! Over there!

450
00:30:27.800 --> 00:30:31.310
H-Hey, you crooks!
What the hell?! Who are you?!

451
00:30:31.310 --> 00:30:33.900
Why are you taking our money?!

452
00:30:33.900 --> 00:30:36.770
Hey! Hold it!

453
00:30:38.330 --> 00:30:39.730
Thanks for the dough!

454
00:30:40.510 --> 00:30:45.190
Give us our money back!
